@geminikq @glenn-jocher 
I have noticed that in the current implementation, w/h of the _current_ image are used in the forward pass (which makes sense) but anchors are not rescaled (not sure that also makes sense). 

When training for a constant image size this of course isn't an issue but I'm not sure whether anchors have to be re-scaled every time the input sizes changes (when training for multi scale).

@nirbenz 
Yes, 0.1 threshold is not mentioned in the paper, I guess it's @glenn-jocher 's method to reduce anchors would be used to predict in the later stage.
for the 0.5-0.7 ignore threshold, maybe the author found 0.7 leads to a better result for coco ? I don't know then. You may try it since you have another GPUs. :-)

for: 
>I have noticed that in the current implementation, w/h of the current image are used in the forward pass (which makes sense) but anchors are not rescaled (not sure that also makes sense).

I don't exactly understand what you refer to. as I know for the implementation, it **IS** rescaled for each image input.
